{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"vegan-forgetful-tiger","description":"# Event-sourced enrichment queue: cert-triggered enqueue, 60-min soak, latest-wins, optimistic claim\n\n## Why\nEnrichment must be async and never on the hot write path. rebar's event store is already a durable, shared, optimistically-concurrent queue substrate — better than any bolted-on SQLite/broker (which cannot live on a shared path nor be visible to all clients). Modeling the queue as events makes \"a new certification replaces the old entry\" the natural latest-wins reduce.\n\n## What\nEnqueue/claim/done modeled as events keyed by `ticket_id`, reduced to current queue state:\n- ENQUEUE appended on plan-review CERTIFICATION with `not_before = cert_time + 60min`; a re-cert appends a new ENQUEUE that supersedes the prior one for that ticket (latest-wins reduce) and bumps `not_before` forward — the soak/debounce, as a stored timestamp filtered at drain (NOT an in-process timer).\n- CLAIM = optimistic-append (only one drainer lands; losers retry another ticket) + a lease with a reaper so a crashed drainer's claim expires → at-least-once → enrichment is idempotent.\n- Wire the ENQUEUE into the plan-review certification path (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/`), using the HLC clock (`.rebar/hlc.state`) for timestamps.\n\n## Scope\n- New queue event types + reducer projection to \"pending / soaking / claimed\" state; a `pending_enrichment(now)` read that returns soaked, unclaimed entries.\n- Enqueue hook on certification; claim/lease/done semantics.\n- IN scope: the queue mechanics + enqueue trigger. OUT: the drain runner (S4), digest production/storage (S1/S2).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Certifying a ticket's plan review enqueues it with `not_before = cert + 60min`; re-certifying supersedes the prior entry and bumps `not_before`.\n- [ ] A drain-time read returns only entries whose `not_before <= now` and that are unclaimed (soak honored; latest-wins per ticket).\n- [ ] Two concurrent claimers of the same entry: exactly one wins (optimistic append), the loser retries — no double-processing under normal operation.\n- [ ] A claim whose lease expires (crashed drainer) is reclaimable; re-processing is safe (idempotent overwrite).\n- [ ] Queue churn stays bounded: latest-wins keeps the reduced pending set at ≤1 entry per ticket regardless of edit bursts.","id":"e1f4-d518-3240-472e","parent_id":"bd83-c56f-1f72-4ef2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Event-sourced enrichment queue: cert-triggered enqueue, 60-min soak, latest-wins, optimistic claim"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783568201313226001,"uuid":"47f8a5b4-0680-4160-b647-30430ad28e29"}